Two men aged 20 and 22 were arrested  late Thursday over an attack on a Syrian asylum-seeker in this east German  town, already the scene of ugly racial attacks in mid-May, police said here  Friday.
The suspects are accused of assaulting and wounding the 25-year-old Syrian  man, who suffered multiple injuries to his head, arms and shoulders Wednesday.  The two are also charged with racketeering a shop and restaurant.
Six people have also been charged with an attack on May 12 against a group  of 60 north Africans in Magdeburg. Twelve people were injured in that attack.
